modules.description: Provides functions to read and write Git objects including blobs, trees, commits, tags, pack files, and index files. Offers operations to make pack files position independent, generate pack indexes, and expand a commit's filesystem. Works with Git-specific data structures and supports both on-disk and in-memory storage.

Provides functions to perform HTTP GET and POST requests with customizable scheme, port, and hostname. Operates with URI structures, error types, and HTTP headers. Used for interacting with Git repositories over HTTP/HTTPS in a non-blocking manner.
